title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 r. 202.70.20 - Temporary Restraining Orders
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 r. 202.70.20 - Temporary Restraining Orders

State Regulations

Unless the moving party can demonstrate
that there will be significant prejudice by reason of giving notice, a
temporary restraining order will not be issued ex parte. The applicant must
give notice, including copies of all supporting papers, to the opposing parties
sufficient to permit them an opportunity to appear and contest the
application. Notes
